# Site context

## Who I am
Solo product and design consultant. I help companies validate a digital product idea
before committing to a full build. My process: discovery, concept, prototype, user testing.

## What I offer
I take a product idea from brief to tested clickable prototype. The output is a validated
concept and a spec that can be handed to a dev team. I can also support as PM during build.

## Primary audience (now)
Companies that need to digitalise or automate a process — reducing admin overhead,
improving internal visibility, or streamlining communication with external users.
Not enterprise software. Practical, high-value products built incrementally.

## Broader audience (over time)
- New founders wanting to validate a business idea before investing in a build
- Existing companies testing a new product feature or adjacent product
- Any organisation that wants to reduce risk before a digital investment

## Tone
Direct, personal, and credible. Not a consulting firm. Not a freelancer pitching cheap work.
Someone with serious experience who works lean and close to the problem.

## What to avoid
- Corporate "we" language
- Vague transformation-speak
- Overpromising on scale or team size